thread.title: Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with Snapdragon 653 and 6GB RAM launched for Rs 36,900
thread.title_full: Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with Snapdragon 653 and 6GB RAM launched for Rs 36,900

title: Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with Snapdragon 653 and 6GB RAM launched for Rs 36,900
text:
Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with Snapdragon 653 and 6GB RAM launched for... Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with Snapdragon 653 and 6GB RAM launched for Rs 36,900 By - January 17, 2017 “The Galaxy C9 Pro is Samsung’s first smartphone to boast 6GB of RAM and a split antenna design” 
Samsung unveiled the Galaxy C9 Pro smartphone in China in October last year. Today, the company has launched the phone in India. The Galaxy C9 Pro is the brand’s first smartphone to boast a beefy 6GB of RAM. The high-end phablet flaunts a metal unibody frame, split antenna band design and a fingerprint sensor that’s embedded into its home button. 
As far as the other specs go, the Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro features a large 6-inch full HD Super AMOLED display, and boots Android Marshmallow with TouchWiz UI on top. The processor under the hood is an octa-core 64-bit Qualcomm Snapdragon 653 processor, coupled with Adreno 510 graphics and 6GB of RAM. It comes with 64GB of internal memory, further expandable via a microSD card. 
The Galaxy C9 Pro sports a 16-megapixel primary shooter with a dual-LED flash and f/1.9 aperture. In the front, the phone houses the same 16-megapixel sensor with f/1.9 aperture, but misses out on a selfie flash. In terms of connectivity, it offers 4G LTE, a USB Type-C port, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and NFC. The phone is backed by a beefy 4,000mAh battery, and measures just 6.9mm around the waist in spite of the huge power cell. 
The Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro has been priced at Rs 36,900 in India, and comes in black and gold hues. The phone will be up for pre-order in the country via select offline stores and e-commerce portals from January 27th. The brand is offering one-time screen replacement for a period of 12 months to those who pre-book the device. In the latter half of February, the phone will be available across channels in the country.
